Main Infrastructure Migration Methods 🖥️

These are specifically for infrastructure layer migration:

1. VM Replication Method

Method:
Entire server copied to cloud.

Process:
Server → Replication agent → Cloud VM

Tools:

AWS MGN
Azure Site Recovery
Google Migrate

Used for:
Infrastructure lift and shift.

2. Image-Based Migration

Method:
Create server image and deploy in cloud.

Process:
Create image → Upload → Launch VM

Example:
VMware image → AWS AMI

Used for:
Standard infrastructure deployment.

3. Containerization Method 📦

Method:
Convert infrastructure into containers.

Process:
Application → Docker → Kubernetes

Benefits:

Portable
Fast scaling
Lightweight

Example:
VM based app → Docker container

4. Infrastructure as Code (IaC) Method 📜

Method:
Infrastructure recreated using scripts.

Tools:

Terraform
AWS CloudFormation
Azure ARM
Pulumi

Example Terraform:

resource "aws_instance" "web" {
  ami = "ami-12345"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"
}

Benefits:

Repeatable infrastructure
Automated deployment
Version control

(This is very important in modern infrastructure migration.)

5. Hybrid Migration Method 🌐

Method:
Part infra on-prem + part cloud.

Example:
Database on-prem
App server in cloud

Used when:

Compliance requirements
Gradual migration needed
6. Blue-Green Migration Method 🔵🟢

Method:
Run old and new infrastructure parallel.

Process:
Old infra (Blue)
New infra (Green)

Switch traffic when ready.

Used for:
Zero downtime migration.

7. Canary Migration 🐤

Method:
Move small traffic first.

Example:
10% users → new infra
If stable → 100%

Used for:
Risk reduction.


